Business Brief -- MIPS Computer Systems Inc.:
   Net of $2.6 Million Posted
   By Company for 4th Period
The company cited higher product demand and reduced
expenses. The results were released after the end of trading
in the company's stock, which was quoted at $11.625, down
62.5 cents in national over-the-counter trading.
   MIPS ended the year with a loss of $34.7 million, or $1.45
a share, mostly because of a third-quarter restructuring
charge of $25.5 million to cut its work-force as well as
reduced licensee payments. In 1990, it earned $7.1 million,
or 28 cents a share. Sales rose 11% to $168.5 million from
$152.3 million.